{"ts": "2026-04-23T21:09:59Z", "event": "clarify_critic", "feature": "build-cortex-setup-subcommand-and-retire-shareable-install-scaffolding", "findings": ["Intent clarity HIGH rests on a still-open fork in the source \u2014 the ticket writes that /setup-merge behavior folds into cortex setup \"or\" into a --merge-settings flag; the assessment treats this as settled when the source defers it.", "Intent clarity HIGH treats the justfile deprecation as settled, but the source says the justfile \"can keep\" a transitional shim for \"one transition release\" \u2014 both are permissive/undefined.", "Scope boundedness HIGH is claimed for --with-extras, but the ticket only says \"registers the cortex-command-plugins marketplace as a convenience (DR-9)\" without stating the registration mechanism or failure semantics.", "Scope boundedness HIGH cites apiKeyHelper preservation as bounded, but the ticket hand-waves to the codebase report rather than defining the constraint inline.", "Requirements alignment HIGH asserts \"no conflicts\" without checking whether moving settings.json deep-merge from an interactive Claude-session skill to a non-interactive CLI subcommand is itself a conflict with quality attributes like Defense-in-depth for permissions.", "Requirements alignment HIGH conflates the distribution constraint (\"local editable install\") with a mandate to migrate just setup functionality into the CLI \u2014 the requirement supports the first but not the second.", "Criticality rationale invokes clarify.md guidance not quoted in the source material, reproducing the gap-filling pattern the review is meant to surface.", "Complexity tier rests partly on a \"potentially apiKeyHelper wiring\" item \u2014 the word \"potentially\" signals uncertainty about whether it is in scope."], "dispositions": {"apply": 0, "dismiss": 6, "ask": 2}, "applied_fixes": [], "dismissals": [{"finding_index": 1, "rationale": "The transitional-shim detail is a minor deprecation-path implementation choice, not a scope uncertainty \u2014 the primary goal (consolidate install surfaces, retire just deploy-*) is clear; transition cadence is a spec-phase detail."}, {"finding_index": 2, "rationale": "The --with-extras mechanism is an implementation detail to be determined in research (DR-9 points to /plugin marketplace add or equivalent); the scope bound is well-defined (register marketplace as a convenience, optional flag, failure-tolerant since it is a convenience)."}, {"finding_index": 3, "rationale": "Reclassified from Ask to Dismiss during self-resolution: apiKeyHelper was already removed from claude/settings.json in shareable-install #004; \"preserve stub semantics\" means do not regress that state and do not reintroduce apiKeyHelper. This is a clear invariant, not an open constraint."}, {"finding_index": 5, "rationale": "The alignment claim is narrower than the critic reads it \u2014 the ticket claims no conflict with the CLI-centric distribution requirement, which is true; the ticket does not need a positive mandate in requirements to be appropriate CLI work."}, {"finding_index": 6, "rationale": "clarify.md IS the rubric the orchestrator applies; citing it is appropriate. The rating itself (high for shared workflow infrastructure) is defensible regardless of whether the rubric is quoted in the ticket body."}, {"finding_index": 7, "rationale": "Even if apiKeyHelper is untouched, the change still crosses 4+ files (cli.py, justfile, skills/setup-merge retirement, claude/settings template handling) and modifies install infrastructure shared across all users \u2014 complex tier holds."}], "status": "ok"}
